== Overview ==
'''Phenomenon 1-B''', also known as ''''No-Clip Disorder'''', is an extremely rare anomaly that manifests in select persons as an almost complete inability to utilize '''[[Phenomenon 1-A]].''' Individuals with the disorder, upon entry to the Backrooms, will find traversing between levels far more difficult, as they are rarely ever able to no-clip and therefore must rely on other methods, such as [[Object 34|'''Elevators''']]. Ironically, '''Phenomenon 1-B''' is considered somewhat of a blessing in the [[The Frontrooms|'''Frontrooms''']] (and is theorized to be preventing most of its population from no-clipping in the first place), but because typical travel methods are unreliable in the Backrooms, it becomes a severe handicap. '''Phenomenon 1-B''' often prevents wanderers from ever traveling beyond '''[[Level 0]],''' and may account for the majority of deaths in said level, though this is unconfirmed.

Of course, the mere existence of '''Phenomenon 1-B''' raises the question of how said wanderers ended up in the Backrooms to begin with. If one cannot no-clip, then it should be impossible to ever leave the [[The Frontrooms|'''Frontrooms''']]. Due to the rarity of the disorder in the Backrooms (and its inherent survival challenges), specialists do not yet have all the answers. If you believe you may have '''No-Clip Disorder''', please contact the [[M.E.G.|'''MEG''']] to be escorted to a safe testing site.

Exactly what causes the manifestation of '''Phenomenon 1-B''' is currently unclear. Theoretically, it should only affect oneself; however, the disorder has been shown to consistently affect group no-clipping attempts. Additionally, it may even dull or negate other anomalous phenomena. Afflicted wanderers have reported significantly lower rates of both resources and entities '''[[Phenomenon 10|Spawning]]'''. While a direct correlation cannot be proven at the moment, this would also contribute to the high death rate of individuals affected by '''Phenomenon 1-B''', since they could not naturally encounter objects like '''[[Object 1|Almond Water]]''' and would be at increased risk of starvation or insanity.

== Discovery ==
'''Phenomenon 1-B''' was first categorized by [[M.E.G.|'''MEG''']] scientists at [[Base Alpha|'''Base Alpha''']] when issues arose using specialized machines to transport a group of refugees to another outpost. Attempting to no-clip all individuals at once continuously failed until onsite recruits suggested clipping one at a time, which was successful for all present wanderers except ███ ████. ███ has remained at Base Alpha and continues to assist in the categorization of new phenomena.

Since initial discovery, '''Phenomenon 1-B''' has reportedly manifested in less than 10 total people, making it one of the rarest afflictions in all of the Backrooms. It seems to be immediately present upon entry from the '''[[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]]''', and has never observably subsided, meaning it is likely a lifelong condition. Afflicted individuals are highly discouraged from exploration beyond '''[[M.E.G.|MEG]]''' sanctioned areas.

